
  <sn><md>#### Ancient Egyptian Civilization {.text-center}

::: .row

::: .col-md-8

The period from `5000–3200 BCE` in Egypt is known as the `Pre-Dynastic Period`. During this time, Egypt was divided into several small city-states known as `Nomes`.

In `3200 BCE`, a king named `Menes` united all of Egypt and established a single unified kingdom. `Memphis`, located in southern Egypt, became its capital. This marked the beginning of the dynastic era in Egypt.

```text id="xjfsyl"
Ancient Egypt
      |
      +--&gt; Nomes (City-States)
      |
      +--&gt; Menes
            |
            +--&gt; Unified Egypt
            +--&gt; Capital: Memphis
```
:::

::: .col-md-4
![img](https://www.egypttoursportal.com/images/2018/01/King-Menes-Narmer-Egypt-Tours-Portal.jpg)
:::

:::
